  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [ ] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen building from source, I was getting this error after updating my system.\r\n\r\n```\r\n.../foundry-rs/foundry/target/release/build/foundry-cli-1fc36a4bcf4e5752/build-script-build: error while loading shared libraries: libgit2.so.1.4: cannot open shared object file: No such file or directory\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe latest release of libgit2 is 1.5, https://archlinux.org/packages/extra/x86_64/libgit2/ and it looks like foundry specifically needs version 1.4.\r\n\r\nCurrently running `5.10.148-1-MANJARO`\r\n\r\n\r\nI was able to get around this problem by installing 1.4 from https://archive.archlinux.org/packages/l/libgit2/ and using `pacman -U` to install 1.4\r\n`\r\nI don't think this is a huge problem since its easy to fix, mostly documenting this for others who may run into the same issue.",
